# Stack rules

## Python (backend)
- Use Python 3.11+ only
- stdlib only: os, pathlib, subprocess, json, uuid
- No third-party packages without explicit approval in CLAUDE.md
- Use pathlib.Path instead of os.path wherever possible
- Use type hints on every function signature
- Format: one function per file is fine, no need to over-abstract

## React / JavaScript (frontend)
- React 18 with functional components only — no class components
- State management: useState and useContext only — no Redux, no Zustand
- Side effects: useEffect only — no lifecycle hacks
- Three.js scenes: always use @react-three/fiber (r3f) Canvas wrapper
  Do not instantiate THREE.Scene manually
- Drei helpers: use @react-three/drei for Text, OrbitControls, Line
- File naming:
  - Components: PascalCase (e.g. ThreeScene.jsx, NodeMesh.jsx)
  - Utilities: camelCase (e.g. buildRingLayout.js, loadTree.js)
  - Tests: same name + .test.js (e.g. buildRingLayout.test.js)

## Styling
- Use inline styles for Three.js overlay UI (Panel.jsx, buttons)
- Use CSS modules for app-level layout (Dashboard.module.css)
- No Tailwind, no styled-components in this project

## General
- Prefer early returns over deeply nested if/else
- No inline TODO comments in committed code — use mvp-1.md instead
- No new dependencies without approval — check package.json before adding
- One component per file, one utility function file per concern